    <h3>Summary: </h3>
    <p>
        The new procedure, PittRigid ME, is a simplified ME design method and a localized design tool are developed for concrete pavement. It is based on the AASHTO MEPDG design procedure but restricts design input parameters to the most influential and relevant for Pennsylvania conditions. It matches the MEPDG predicted performance at a fraction of the computational cost.

    </p>

    <p><span class="font-weight-bold">Character:</span>Mechanistic-empirical (ME) design tool for new jointed plain concrete pavement (JPCP) </p>


    <p><span class="font-weight-bold">Developer:</span>Lev Khazanovich and Haoran Li. </p>
    <p>
        PittRigid ME was developed at the University of Pittsburgh under the sponsorship of the IRISE Consortium.

    </p>

